songs.title: Royals (Cover)
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1: Normani & Lauren]
I've never seen a diamond in the flesh
I cut my teeth on wedding rings in the movies
And I'm not proud of my address
In the torn up town, no post code envy

[Pre-Chorus: Dinah & Normani]
But every song's like gold teeth, Grey Goose, trippin' in the bathroom
Bloodstains, ball gowns, trashin' the hotel room
We don't care; we're driving Cadillacs in our dreams
But everybody's like Cristal, Maybach, diamonds on your timepiece
Jet planes, islands, tigers on a gold leash
We don't care; we aren't caught up in your love affair

[Chorus: Ally & Lauren & (All) & Dinah + Normani & {Camila}]
And we'll never be royals (royals)
It don't run in our blood
That kind of luxe just ain't for us
We crave a different kind of buzz
Let me be your ruler (ruler)
You can call us Queen Bee
And baby I'll rule (I'll rule I'll rule I'll rule...)
{Let me live that fantasy}

[Bridge: (All) & Camila & Dinah]
(Oooh ooooh no-o-o-o ohhh)
We're bigger than we ever dreamed
And I'm in love with being queen
(Oooooh ohhhhh ooooh, oooh)
Life is great, without a care
We aren't caught up in your love affair

[Chorus: Ally & Lauren & (All) & Dinah + Normani & {Camila}]
And we'll never be royals (royals)
It don't run in our blood
That kind of luxe just ain't for us
We crave a different kind of buzz
Let me be your ruler (ruler)
You can call us Queen Bee
And baby I'll rule (I'll rule I'll rule I'll rule...)
{Let me live that fantasy}
